OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FMorning low cloud will quickly
OL,6,Fburn away to leave another widely dry
OL,7,Fand sunny day. A little fair weather
OL,8,Fcloud may bubble up later, especially
OL,9,Ftowards the southeast. Breezy,
OL,10,Fespecially over the hills but feeling
OL,11,Fvery warm in shelter.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FA fine and dry evening with
OL,14,Fplenty of late sunshine. Overnight
OL,15,Fwill stay dry with further clear
OL,16,Fskies. A warm night to come,
OL,17,Fespecially in the towns and cities.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
